##########Base
pipe basics~[keywords]~search for YouTube videos
pipe basics~[youtube-url]~play a video by YouTube URL
pipe basics~:v(ideoid)=ID~play videos by YouTube video IDs
pipe basics~[playlist-url]~display videos from a playlistURL
pipe basics~:playlist=ID~display videos from a playlistID
##########Control
pipe control~:n(ext)~get the next page of results
pipe control~:b(ack~get the previous page of results
##########Actions
pipe actions~:login~will prompt you for login
pipe actions~:logout~will delete the authentication key
##########YouTube
pipe tube~:i(nfo)=i,i~display more information
pipe tube~:d(ownload)=i,i~download the selected videos
pipe tube~:c(omments)=i~display video comments
pipe tube~:r(elated)=i~display related videos
pipe tube~:u(ploads)=i~display author's latest uploads
pipe tube~:pv=i :popular=i~display author's popular uploads
pipe tube~:A(ctivity)=i~display author's recent activity
pipe tube~:p(laylists)=i~display author's playlists
pipe tube~:ps=i :s2p=i,i~save videos to a post-selected playlist
pipe tube~:subscribe=i~subscribe to author's channel
pipe tube~:(dis)like=i~like or dislike a video
pipe tube~:fav(orite)=i~favorite a video
pipe tube~:autoplay=i~autoplay mode, starting from video i
##########Playing
pipe play~<number>~play the corresponding video
pipe play~3-8, 3..8~same as 3 4 5 6 7 8
pipe play~8-3, 8..3~same as 8 7 6 5 4 3
pipe play~8 2 12 4 6 5 1~play the videos in a specific order
pipe play~10..~play all the videos onwards from 10
pipe play~:q(ueue)=i,i,...~enqueue videos for playing them later
pipe play~:pq, :play-queue~play the enqueued videos (if any)
pipe play~:anp, :nnp~auto-next-page, no-next-page
pipe play~:play=i,i,...~play a group of selected videos
pipe play~:regex=my?[regex]~play videos matched by a regex (/i)
pipe play~:kregex=KEY,RE~play videos if the value of KEY matches the RE
##########Others
pipe more~:r(eturn)~return to previous page of results
pipe more~:refresh~refresh the current list of results
pipe more~:dv=i~display the data structure of result i
pipe more~-argv -argv2=v~apply some arguments (e.g.: -u=google)
pipe more~:reset, :reload~restart the application
pipe more~:q, :quit, :exit~close the application
